HEADWORD: Clusiaceae
<hw>Clusiaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a widely distributed family of
chiefly tropical trees and shrubs and vines that produce oils and resins
and some usable timber.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Guttiferae, family <fam>Guttiferae</fam>, family
<fam>Clusiaceae</fam>, St John's wort family.</syn>⟦br⟧
